The paper discusses the use of artificial neural networks and decision trees for feature selection and encoding relevant features and their interactions into the neural network. This work falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it deals with learning methods and model selection. Additionally, the use of decision trees for feature selection and encoding makes it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data mining (cs.DM) subcategories. The neural network aspect also makes it relevant to neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV) subcategories.
